#
# this is HW/SW regression demo
# HW part: using verilog to implement it (ex: add func)
# SW part: using verilog vpi to call c/c++ func (ex: + )
# assertion check : check the HW and SW results are eq
# register all testsuites to python unittest flow
# ex: ./test/test_dut.v

#system requirement
# 1. iverilog
#   mac install  % port install iverilog
# 2. nose
#   mac install  % port install nose or easy_install nose
# 3. python2.7
# 4. vpi verilog interface(it's include in iverilog)
# 5. make sure your env path is include the iverlog, python, nose....
# ex: .bashrc
#
# how to run it
# % python regression.py

Ref:
1. how to use VPI in iverilog
  http://iverilog.wikia.com/wiki/Using_VPI
2. vpi log10 example
  http://www.project-veripage.com/math_p2.php
3. run VPI example
  http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Verilog_Procedural_Interface

iverilog command
ref: ./vpi/runtest.sh
